      "raw_text": "SEATTLE, Aug. THE Joint\nhouse and senate investigating\ncommittee is determined to inves-\ntigate the office of the state land\ncommissioner. according to Chair\nman Pliny l.. Allen today. He said\nthe committee is determined to as\ncertain what has become of all\nlands the government gave the\nstate of Washington under the en-\nabling act of 1889. The committee\nwill get a record of all sales and\nlist of the land left. Land Commits\nsioner Rose has such a list, but\nAllen says the committee has de-\nclined to consult 1t, A separate\nforce of clerks are working for the\ncommittee, getting information\nfrom the federal land offices\nthroughout the state."
    }
  ]
